Candle Shop Java Program
This is a basic Java program that simulates a candle shop. The program allows users to select different candles, specify quantities, and generates a receipt displaying the details of the purchased candles.

How to Run
Make sure you have Java installed on your machine.
Compile the CandleShop.java file using a Java compiler.
Run the compiled program using the command java CandleShop.
Follow the on-screen instructions to input the quantities of desired candles.
The program will display a receipt with details of the selected candles and the total.
Candles Available
The program offers a variety of candles with different burn times and prices. You can choose the quantity of each candle you'd like to purchase.

Output
The program will generate a receipt displaying the following information for each selected candle:

Candle name
Amount purchased
Burn time
Dollar per burn time
Price
Additionally, the receipt will show the following totals:

Total burn time
Total dollar per burn time
Total price